<emphasis id="CFDBEAEF9066FF9BB12716EBFAA7FE19" box="[1308,1351,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">sulc</emphasis>
- means furrow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B5B565769066FF9BB4FC1513FD82FD69" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FD1036FD9066FF9BB4FC1513FD82FD69" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,643]" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">
<emphasis id="CFDBEAEF9066FF9BB4FC1513FEA6FDD1" bold="true" box="[199,326,547,571]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" reason="1">Discussion.</emphasis>
This new species can be distinguished from the known species of this genus by the morphology of male tenth abdominal tergite: basal half bulged; apical half narrow, nearly rectangular, with a very obvious furrow on dorsal surface, almost vertically bent downwards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
